scopeContent.description:
'Photograph of oil painting. Picture by E Long RA, entitled 'The Baylonian Marriage Market' in the Royal Holloway College Gallery. A row of maidens arranged in the order of their beauty extends along the lower part of the picture from right to left, they are facing the spectator. Above to the left the auctioneer is offering the first and most beautiful girl who is posed with her back to the spectator, standing on a raised dais with an attendant unveiling her. Beyond and in the background, the audience fills the room. Eastern characters and figures decorate the walls of the apartment'.
